Anime
A two-episode mini anime adaptation of the series was announced on October 31, 2020. The first episode was streamed on November 7, 2020, on Comic Fire's official Twitter account, followed by the second episode on November 14.
On November 29, 2021, a new anime adaptation was announced. It was later revealed to be a television series produced by Studio Comet. The series is directed by Naoyuki Kuzuya, with scripts written by Mitsutaka Hirota, character designs handled by Reiichirō Ōfuji, and music composed by Kenta Higashiohji. It aired from January 10 to March 28, 2023, on TV Tokyo and other networks. The opening theme song is "Day1" by Auo featuring Win Morisaki, while the ending theme song is  by Yui Nishio. Crunchyroll streamed the series worldwide outside of Asia. Muse Communication licensed the series in Asia-Pacific.
